stockTrapString.name: stockTrapString
stockTrapString.description: The message defined for the event that triggers a trap.

dlStockTrap.name: dlStockTrap
dlStockTrap.description: The stock trap is issued when a data, no data, scheduled, percent full, or test trap event happens.

dlStockDbasePfullTrap.name: dlStockDbasePfullTrap
dlStockDbasePfullTrap.description: The stock database percent full trap is issued when the database size surpasses the threshold.

dlStockDataAlarmTrap.name: dlStockDataAlarmTrap
dlStockDataAlarmTrap.description: The stock data alarm trap is issued when a data alarm happens.

dlStockNoDataAlarmTrap.name: dlStockNoDataAlarmTrap
dlStockNoDataAlarmTrap.description: The stock no-data alarm trap is issued when the unit has received no data for a configured interval within a configured schedule.

dlStockSchedTrap.name: dlStockSchedTrap
dlStockSchedTrap.description: The stock scheduled alarm trap is issued when the current time reaches the scheduled alarm time.

dlStockImmediateTrap.name: dlStockImmediateTrap
dlStockImmediateTrap.description: The stock immediate alarm trap is issued when the user enters the DOTRAP command.

dlStockSocketLostTrap.name: dlStockSocketLostTrap
dlStockSocketLostTrap.description: The stock socket lost trap is issued when the IPRC socket is disconnected.
